sentences.english: Facts and figures starting to blend together in a horrible haze?
sentences.chinese: 事实和数字开始混淆在一起让你摸不着头脑？

sentences.english: The purpose of this enclosure remains as mysterious as this whole structure.
sentences.chinese: 这种包围的意图正如整个结构一样让人摸不着头脑。

sentences.english: Yet this end-of-December madness makes no sense to me.
sentences.chinese: 可他们这12月底的疯狂却始终让我摸不着头脑。

sentences.english: And of course, the cultural references are likely to boggle your mind.
sentences.chinese: 当然，里面的文化内容可能会让你摸不着头脑。

sentences.english: And yesterday's Huanshuai was so sudden, people have been speaking Greek.
sentences.chinese: 而昨日的换帅又是如此突然，让人摸不着头脑。

sentences.english: I will not confuse my master by throwing snowballs for him to fetch.
sentences.chinese: 我不会把雪球扔出去让主人捡，弄的他摸不着头脑。

sentences.english: China's domestic bond market is a murky work-in-progress.
sentences.chinese: 国国内债券市场是个让人摸不着头脑的“在建工程”。

sentences.english: We are talking about, Joji monks scratching their heads.
sentences.chinese: 大家都议论纷纷，丈二的和尚摸不着头脑。

sentences.english: Other conspiracy theories about Mr Obama are even loopier.
sentences.chinese: 其他版本的奥巴马阴谋论更让人摸不着头脑。

sentences.english: Andof course, the cultural referencesarelikely boggle your mind.
sentences.chinese: 当然，里面的文化内容可能会让你摸不着头脑。

sentences.english: She just stared vacantly and said things that made no sense.
sentences.chinese: 她只是呆望着，嘴里说的东西也常常让人摸不着头脑。

sentences.english: One diet that continues to confound nutritionists is the French diet.
sentences.chinese: 更让营养学家摸不着头脑的饮食习惯是法国。

sentences.english: I have absolutely no idea why, but the crocodile suddenly raced across the backs of the hippos.
sentences.chinese: 我是绝对摸不着头脑，鳄鱼为什么顺着河马的背跑。
